race.comment: SHORT STRAW (6) missed the placings when resuming two runs back then did a good job last start but found a couple better over 1100m at Toodyay, beaten only 1.5 lengths after being in contention on the turn. Fitter for that run and if she adopts similar tactics today, she'll be hard to mow down. ORKNEY LAD (2) finished out of the money two starts back then he got a long way back and was beaten 3 lengths when eighth in a 1000m contest at Bunbury three-and-a-half weeks ago. Faces an easier assignment so he is a major player. NIGHT GUARDIAN (3) finished 2.5 lengths away in fourth after being in the firing line on the turn at his last appearance over 1190m at Moora on October 4. Expected to feature in the finish this time. ARCHENEMY (4) has trialled well coming into this and can feature with the blinkers on first time. GREY REVOLUTION (5) is best of the rest.
